BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:6bsaH7pGAGAFt8Bxx33Cg
SUMMARY:Crush: My Year as an Apprentice Winemaker with Nicholas O’Connell
DTSTAMP:20260330T060559Z
DTSTART:20260330T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:Folio: The Seattle Athenaeum is delighted to welcome author and
	 Folio member Nicholas O'Connell for a behind-the-scenes look at the daily
	 operations of some of the world's most prestigious wineries on the West C
	oast in his latest book Crush: My Year as an Apprentice Winemaker . This i
	nsider's view of the wine world includes the intense competition for the b
	est grapes\, the bizarre lingo of the tasting rooms\, and the visionary wi
	nemakers who magically transform grapes into high-end wine. It is a world 
	that includes not only romance and refinement but long hours\, backbreakin
	g labor\, mind-numbing repetition\, and fanatical dedication to quality. S
	uch devotion resulted in the 1973 Stag's Leap Wine Cellars Cabernet that w
	on the best red wine at the 1976 Judgment of Paris and transformed the U.S
	. wine industry. O'Connell's quest to master the art of wine making begins
	 in his garage. From there he embarks on an apprenticeship at Betz and DeL
	ille Cellar and other great wineries in California\, Or\n\nhttps://www.fol
	ioseattle.org/event-details/crush-my-year-as-an-apprentice-winemaker-with-
	nicholas-oconnell\n\nFrom Pike Place Market Events
URL:https://www.folioseattle.org/event-details/crush-my-year-as-an-apprenti
	ce-winemaker-with-nicholas-oconnell
LOCATION:Folio: The Seattle Athenaeum\, 93 Pike St. #307
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:events
CATEGORIES:Pike Place Market Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
